{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Grease and line a spring form cake tin (Ø 22 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Insert simmering basket and weigh mandarins into it. Add water to mixing bowl and cook <nobr>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set mandarins aside to cool. Empty mixing bowl.","Place cooled whole mandarins in mixing bowl and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat blending <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl. <strong><br><\/strong> ","Place macadamia nuts and almonds in mixing bowl then mill <nobr>30 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with mandarin purée and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place caster sugar and 250 g butter in mixing bowl then whip <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add eggs and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Add reserved mandarin purée, reserved crushed nuts, polenta and baking powder then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr> if necessary.","Transfer cake batter to prepared tin, then bake for 60-70 minutes (170°C) or until a wooden skewer inserted in the centre of the cake comes out clean. Allow to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes), then dust with icing sugar before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["250 g butter, soft, plus extra for greasing","320 g mandarins (approx. 4), unpeeled","1000 g water","60 g whole raw macadamia nuts","220 g blanched almonds","220 g caster sugar","3 eggs","170 g polenta","1 tsp gluten free baking powder","icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r146866","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-YySh2mXdeYw\/XZWqoK6TjPI\/AAAAAAAAfa0\/Y5OnLcbKAIsjupOr-uam8HPhUn-b9Z1jwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0